        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:35PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 334 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Chavistown to near Maxton. Movement was
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bennettsville, Red Springs, Maxton, Mccoll, Shannon, Buie, Wakulla,
Chavistown, Prospect, Rex, Wallace, Gibson, Rennert, Lumber Bridge,
and Tatum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
